  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to death caused by prolonged exposure to extreme environmental conditions, typically severe cold or heat, without adequate protection or shelter. This condition is also known as **hypothermia** when it results from extreme cold or **hyperthermia** when it results from extreme heat.\n\n### Causes:\n1. **Hypothermia (Cold Exposure):**  \n   - Occurs when the body loses heat faster than it can produce it, causing the core body temperature to drop dangerously low.  \n   - Symptoms include shivering, confusion, drowsiness, and eventual organ failure.  \n\n2. **Hyperthermia (Heat Exposure):**  \n   - Occurs when the body overheats due to prolonged exposure to high temperatures or physical exertion in hot environments.  \n   - Conditions like heat exhaustion or heat stroke can lead to organ damage and death.  \n\n### Factors Contributing to Exposure Deaths:\n- Lack of shelter or appropriate clothing.  \n- Prolonged time in harsh environments (e.g., wilderness, deserts, or icy conditions).  \n- Dehydration, exhaustion, or underlying health conditions.  \n\n### Prevention:\n- Wearing weather-appropriate clothing.  \n- Seeking shelter and staying hydrated.  \n- Recognizing early symptoms of hypothermia or hyperthermia.  \n\nDying from exposure is a significant risk in survival situations, outdoor activities, or for vulnerable populations like the homeless.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
